data.description: Welcome to your future home at 18 Butler St, Rome, GA 30161, a charming and  updated residence that's now looking for its new owners. This inviting house, featuring 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and distinguished by its impressive 10 ft high ceilings, promises a spacious and airy living experience. The interior delights with white soft-closed cabinets, adding a touch of elegance and functionality to your daily living.    Spanning a generous lot, this property offers ample outdoor space to create your private oasis or host memorable gatherings with friends and family. The meticulously maintained exterior, complemented by a roof installed less than 3 years ago, ensures peace of mind for years to come.    Strategically situated, this home places you in perfect proximity to key community features. Education is at your doorstep with the Floyd County Schools College & Career Academy just over a mile away, ensuring your family's academic needs are easily met. For your grocery needs, Publix Super Market at Charles Hight Square is conveniently located less than a mile away. Your leisure and recreation are also covered with Parks Hoke Park within walking distance, offering a serene escape from daily life. Downtown Rome, with its diverse array of dining, shopping, and entertainment options, is mere minutes away, promising a vibrant lifestyle. Additionally, peace of mind is assured with the Floyd Medical Center close by for any healthcare needs.    This property not only offers a comfortable and stylish living space but also an unbeatable location that puts all conveniences within easy reach. It's an ideal blend of practicality, style, and convenience, making it the perfect choice for anyone looking to make Rome, GA their new home. Don't miss out on this opportunity to own a piece of this friendly community.
